HEADWORD: Leucoxene
<hw>Leu*cox"ene</hw> <pr>(l⟦usl⟧*k⟦ocr⟧ks"⟦emac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Leuco-</ets> + Gr. <grk>xe`nos</grk> stranger.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A nearly opaque white mineral, in part identical
with titanite, observed in some igneous rocks as the result of the
alteration of titanic iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

